content.description: The crux is in the middle of the route.  The line is another lap after leading Dog & Pony Show.
content.protection: TR from the shared anchor with Dog & Pony Show. Stop at the ledge and stay way from the large loose flake below the anchor.
content.location: The route is the crack weakness just right of the smooth face of Dogma.

climbs.name: Skinny Puppy
climbs.fa: Karl Kiser, Alex Sfakianos, Mark Grazier, Anna Brown & Kayla Bouch:  spring 2018

content.description: The crux is on the smooth rock in the center of the route.  It is some of sort of easier 5.10 and there are several ways to climb the crux.
content.protection: 5 bolts to a chain and bolt anchor.
content.location: The route is on the left of the Doghouse on the smaller formation.

climbs.name: Puppy Love
climbs.fa: Anna Brown, Karl Kiser & Cynthia Adams--spring 2018

content.description: The crux is around the 5th bolt.  This is a new Diablo route, watch the smaller holds.
content.protection: 6 bolts to a bolt and chain anchor.  Rap the route.
content.location: This is the last route on the left of the Doghouse.  There is a smaller face below the pinnacle.

climbs.name: Dogma
climbs.fa: Rich Strang, Leo Santibanez, Daniel Berry

content.description: Climbs the super smooth rock just right if the corner/gully. A very hard move at the bottom gives way to easier fun climbing on the smooth slab to the anchor
content.protection: TR only for now, can be accessed by swinging/tensioning over from Dog & Pony Show
content.location: just right of the main right facing corner/gully

content.description: Rightmost route at present. Start up blobby vertical rock that looks loose but is solid. Continue up the easy slab to a vertical face characterized by high feet and long reaches to good holds. A final steep section offers some more technical feet and some fun pocket pulling to the chains.

climbs.name: Dog & Pony Show
climbs.fa: Rich Strang, Leo Santibanez, Daniel Berry

content.description: The center route on the cliff. Similar vertical start to DogGone It. After the slab there is a vertical bulge crux at mid route. Continue past this on nice, featured, vertical rock to the anchors
content.location: Center of the main Dog House cliff

content.description: This is the small cliff/landmass that is south and west of The Shack area. You continue hiking south past that area to a second small valley. The cliff faces east so it gets early morning sun (though not as quick as Winter Wall). In summer (the main Shack season) you probably need to be on the routes early since it gets hot. During the spring and fall seasons these are the perfect warm-ups since the usual shaded warm-ups at the Shack are often quite chilly. The rock is extremely clean basalt, similar to The Overlook and is slabby and vertical in nature. "Old School" slab/face climbs but very enjoyable.
